github-backup - GitHub Repository Backup

USAGE:
    github-backup [project1] [project2] ...

DESCRIPTION:
    Backup git projects to GitHub repositories. Creates repositories
    if they don't exist, sets up remotes, and syncs all branches and tags.

ARGUMENTS:
    project1, project2, ...
        Specific projects to backup (optional, defaults to all)

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-github-git-projects-path PATH
        Path containing git projects to backup

    -git-username USERNAME
        GitHub username

EXAMPLES:
    github-backup
    github-backup project1 project2
